headline: Why Morgan Stanley Offers A Compelling Long-Term Investor Story
summary: Morgan Stanley (NYSE:MS) on Wednesday reported a second-quarter 2025 earnings of $2.13, up from $1.82 a year ago and beating the consensus of $2.02. Net earnings increased to $3.54 billion from $3.08 billion. The U.S. bank reported revenue of $16.79 billion, up 12% year over year, beating the consensus of $16.11 billion. Despite the positive headline figures, Morgan Stanley’s stock reacted negatively after the earnings release, according to Bank of America (BofA) Securities. Also Read: JPMorgan’
